                    "company": "Port of Rotterdam",
                    "description": "After my graduation assignment at Port of Rotterdam I started working as Management Trainee - Digital transition & Innovation. Port of Rotterdams management traineeship is a 2-year young talent program, focused on personal development & leadership. It is build on four pillars: \n\n1. Learning on the job via a rotational program, completing 4 different projects\n2. A personal development program facilitated by an external training & development institute\n3. Mentorship and guidance from MT member and external career coach\n4. A strategic group assigment sponsored by a board member.\n\nBrief summary of assignments and responsibilities:\n1th- Innovation department \u2013 Gathering and communicating the latest (technical) innovations. And developing a database of promising start- and scale-ups by industry relevant for Port of Rotterdam.\n2nd- Corporate strategy \u2013 Facilitating the strategy development and alignment to our corporate strategy for multiple value teams after a reorganization. Besides many (smaller) strategic evaluations, vision documents and data visualisations.\n3th- Harbour master division \u2013 The project management of implementing a new international digital standard for berths at Port of Rotterdam involving external stakeholders. Responsible for the client-validation of berth data of all terminals in Rotterdam (>200 companies)\n4th -Strategic finance department \u2013 The financial modeling and financial viability evaluation (go/no-go) for the next funding round (2.4M) of a digital product.\n\nBesides the four assignments, together with our CIO I have designed  a strategic digital vision on our port, the Port Reference Architecture. This framework is used in the company as leading digital strategic framework for our board and supervisory board, more information can also be found in our latest annual report.",
                    "title": "Management Trainee - Digital Transition and Innovation",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
